In this press briefing, Press Secretary Robert Gibbs discusses a meeting with Democratic leadership, the next three agenda items, financial reform, unemployment insurance, and small business lending. He also discusses the drilling moratorium, the new budget director, deficit figures, increased taxes, the referendum in southern Sudan, poll numbers, and the Gulf oil spill. Gibbs also talks about the President's speeches, the upcoming Chamber of Commerce summit, Jack Lew's nomination for OMB director, energy legislation, unemployment benefits, and the Iranian scientist who sought refuge in the Pakistani embassy. He also mentions the upcoming visit of the Prime Minister of Great Britain, Khalid Sheikh Mohammed's trial, messaging, immigration, and the death of George Steinbrenner.